title: A 'leading explanation' is 3 downed objects were commercial, benign balloons: WH
description: White House spokesperson John Kirby told ABC's "Good Morning America" it could "take us a while" to collect and analyze debris from the downed objects.
author: Justin Gomez, Alexandra Hutzler, Trish Turner, Allison Pecorin

title: GOP Senators Filled the 2016 Debate Stage. Not This Time.
description: Family time. Desire to reshape the party. Attachment to the US Senate. These are the reasons ambitious but low-polling Republican senators cite for avoiding a toe-to-toe contest with former President Donald Trump to be the GOP’s 2024 nominee.
author: Steven T. Dennis, Laura Litvan

title: Tom Cotton: Biden Administration Owes 'Explanation' for 'Objects' Shot Out of Sky
description: The Biden administration owes an "explanation" for the "objects" that jets have shot out of the sky in recent days, Sen. Tom Cotton (R-AR) said in a statement Monday.
author: Hannah Bleau, Hannah Bleau

title: Cotton: 'The American People Deserve an Explanation' from Biden over Chinese Balloon
description: During an appearance on Monday's broadcast of Fox News Channel's "The Ingraham Angle," Sen. Tom Cotton (R-AR) said the public was owed an explanation from the Biden administration for the alleged Chinese spy balloon and other objects the U.S. military had sho…
author: Jeff Poor, Jeff Poor

title: 10 GOP Senators to Host Fundraiser for Jim Banks at Campaign Committee HQ
description: Ten Republican senators are hosting a fundraiser for Rep. Jim Banks (R-IN), who is running for the U.S. Senate in Indiana, in late March at the Senate Republican's campaign committee headquarters.
author: Jacob Bliss, Jacob Bliss

title: Rubio Reintroduces Bipartisan TikTok Ban, Says ‘Momentum Is Growing’ to Pass Bill
description: Sen. Marco Rubio (R-FL) reintroduced a bill with Sen. Angus King (I-ME) on Friday to ban TikTok unless the app is fully divested of Chinese ownership, announcing that “momentum is growing” to pass the legislation.
author: Ashley Oliver, Ashley Oliver

title: Arkansas Delegation Presses Biden Energy Department on $200M Federal Grant Awarded to CCP-Linked Company
description: The Republican Arkansas delegation is demanding answers from the Department of Energy as to why it awarded a $200 million grant to a company linked to the Chinese Communist Party (CCP) using American taxpayer money that was supposed to be used to make America…
author: Kristina Wong, Kristina Wong

title: Cotton: Biden Admin. 'Excusing' and 'Apologizing for' China by Claiming Balloon Was Blown off Course
description: On Thursday’s broadcast of the Fox News Channel’s “America’s Newsroom,” Sen. Tom Cotton (R-AR) reacted to an anonymous official claiming that the Chinese spy balloon was intended to go over Guam and Hawaii, but was blown off course by saying that
author: Ian Hanchett, Ian Hanchett

title: Cotton: W.H.O. 'in the Pocket of' the CCP and Biden Has Acted 'Just Like' Them on COVID Origins
description: On Thursday’s broadcast of the Fox News Channel’s “America’s Newsroom,” Sen. Tom Cotton (R-AR) stated that the World Health Organization’s announcement that it is abandoning the second phase of its investigation into the origins of the coronavirus shows that …
author: Ian Hanchett, Ian Hanchett

title: Relax, those objects in the sky are probably just from one of the 90 countries and 10,000 companies that make up the nearly $1 trillion space economy
description: The three UFOs the US shot down last weekend might not belong to China or aliens. There's a good chance they had ties to the growing space economy.
author: jzinkula@insider.com (Jacob Zinkula)

title: Ted Cruz recommits to 2024 Senate run
description: Cruz tells his supporters on a call that he is focused on his Senate seat "so we can keep Texas red."
author: Caroline Linton

title: Lawmakers mock Biden after UFO address: 'CCP is laughing at him'
description: Sens. Tom Cotton and Dan Sullivan criticized Biden's address Thursday on the Chinese spy balloon and other unidentified aerial objects that were shot down recently.
author: Brianna Herlihy

title: Cotton slams VP Harris for 'refusing to acknowledge' scale of China threat
description: Sen. Tom Cotton slammed Vice President Kamala Harris for saying the recent U.S. downing of a Chinese surveillance balloon shouldn't impact relations between Washington and Beijing.
author: Aaron Kliegman

title: Senators take aim at Biden's support for bill giving illegals, Chinese Communist Party members right to vote
description: Sens. Katie Britt, R-Ala., and Tom Cotton, R-Ark., are taking aim at President Biden's support for a D.C. Council bill that would give illegal immigrants the right to vote.
author: Brandon Gillespie

title: Republicans blast Biden after latest inflation report, say president 'living in an alternate reality'
description: Congressional Republicans tore into President Biden after the latest inflation report saw prices in the U.S. rise by 0.5 percent over the month of January.
author: Houston Keene

title: US diplomat apologizes for tweet gone 'awry' saying Afghan women need 'movement' similar to 'Black Girl Magic'
description: U.S. Chargé d’Affaires Karen B. Decker apologized after her tweet saying that Afghan girls need a "movement" similar to "Black Girl Magic" sparked major backlash.
author: Brianna Herlihy

title: US 'can't find' remnants of downed 'objects,' Kennedy says, as Blumenthal calls for more transparency
description: Lawmakers called for more transparency from President Biden on the unidentified flying objects that were shot down over the U.S. and Canada since Feb. 4.
author: Chris Pandolfo, Kelly Phares

title: US diplomat scorched for 'tone-deaf' tweet saying Afghan women need 'movement' similar to 'Black Girl Magic'
description: United States Chargé d’Affaires Karen B. Decker raised eyebrows with a since-deleted tweet suggesting Afghan women need a "Black Girl Magic" movement.
author: Bailee Hill

title: Rand Paul takes aim at ‘injustice’ of health facilities that deny care to unvaxxed patients
description: The legislation from Sen. Rand Paul would bar federal funds from going to health care facilities that have denied patients care based on their COVID-19 vaccination status.
author: Kelly Laco | Fox News

title: Some Democrats call on White House to tell the public more about flying objects
description: Some Senate Democrats said Wednesday that the American people deserve to hear more about the unidentified aerial objects that were shot down over North America.
author: Scott Wong and Julie Tsirkin and Liz Brown-Kaiser and Kate Santaliz

title: Unidentified Objects Downed Over U.S. Could Deliver a Big Win for the GOP
description: Reports of foreign objects flying over the country are prompting calls from Republicans to rule out defense budget cuts.

title: What the U.S. Is Doing To Curtail Chinese Land Ownership
description: National and state lawmakers are proposing bills that would ban or limit Chinese investment in U.S. land, citing national security concerns.
author: Aleks Phillips

title: Nikki Haley Comes Out Swinging for Trump
description: Haley officially launched her 2024 bid for President on Wednesday with a call to reject ideas and candidates that have kept the GOP away from the White House.
author: Nick Reynolds

title: U.S. gives farmers shorter window to spray crop chemical dicamba
description: The U.S. Environmental Protection Agency said on Thursday it had slightly shortened the window for farmers in major soybean-producing states to use a weedkiller criticized for drifting away from where it is sprayed.

title: Chinese spy balloon has GOP saying no cuts to defense
description: A growing number of Senate Republicans are saying that President Biden and Speaker Kevin McCarthy (R-Calif.) should take defense spending cuts off the table ...
